$ SQLite: blob datatype

A value whose → development/databases/SQLite/datatypes[data type] is *blob* can be created with the
→ development/databases/SQLite/functions[functions] → development/databases/SQLite/functions/zeroblob[`zeroblob(n)`] and → development/databases/SQLite/functions/randomblob[`randomblob(n)`] or the «blob literal» `x'…'`.

A hexadecimal representation of the blob-value is returned by the functions 
→ development/databases/SQLite/functions/quote[`hex(blob_value)`] or
→ development/databases/SQLite/functions/quote[`quote(blob_value)`].

gh|about-sqlite|/datatypes/blob/use.sql||

sa:
  → development/databases/SQLite/datatypes[SQLite data types]
